Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on automatic speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with speech signals and their processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of end-to-end models for speech recognition, which involves training a class-based language model and using a token passing decoder. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel method to improve the performance of end-to-end models for speech recognition, which involves using a class-based language model and a token passing decoder. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new system for speech recognition that involves a class-based language model and a token passing decoder.
